{"lemma":"شاعِراتٌ","slug":"شاعِراتٌ","root":"ش.ع.ر","root_slug":"ش-ع-ر","root_link":"/words/roots/ش-ع-ر","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"شاعِر","root":"شعر","pos":"N","occurrence_count":5},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":3},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["","n22491"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B4%D8%A7%D8%B9%D9%90%D8%B1%D8%A7%D8%AA%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"poet","examples":[{"text":"وَٱلشُّعَرَآءُ يَتَّبِعُهُمُ ٱلۡغَاوُۥنَ","english":"As for poets, they are followed ˹merely˺ by deviants"}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"bard"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to vie as a poet with"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Derived from the active participle of شَعَرَ (šaʕara, “to know”)."},"ipa":["/ʃaː.ʕir/","/ʃaː.ʕa.ra/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n22491","headword_ar":"شَاعِرٌ","root":"$Er","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A poet:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, S, Msb, K:) so called because of his intelligence; (S, Msb;) or because he knows what others know not: (T, TA:) accord. to Akh, it is a possessive epithet, like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laAbinN","text_ar":"لَابِنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taAmirN","text_ar":"تَامِرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$uEaraA='u","text_ar":"شُعَرَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb, K,) deviating from analogy: (S, Msb:) Sb says that the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faAEilN","text_ar":"فَاعِلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is likened in this case to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faEiylN","text_ar":"فَعِيلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and hence this pl.: (TA:) or, accord. to IKh, the pl. is of this form because the sing. is from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aEura","text_ar":"شَعُرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and therefore should by rule be of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faEiylN","text_ar":"فَعِيلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ariyfN","text_ar":"شَرِيفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$arufa","text_ar":"شَرُفَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; but were it so, it might be confounded with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aEiyr","text_ar":"شَعِير"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning the grain thus called, therefore they said"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aAEirN","text_ar":"شَاعِرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and regarded in the pl. the original form of the sing. (Msb.) A wonderful poet is called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xino*iy*N","text_ar":"خِنْذِيذٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": one next below him,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aAEirN","text_ar":"شَاعِرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": then, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$awayoEirN","text_ar":"شَوَيْعِرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[the dim.]: (Yoo, K:) then, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$uEoruwrN","text_ar":"شُعْرُورٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": and then, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mata$aAEirN","text_ar":"مَتَشَاعِرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.) ―         -b2-  Also (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A liar:"},{"kind":"text","text":"because of the many lies in poetry: and so, accord. to some, in the Kur xxi. 5. (B, TA.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$iEorN $aAEirN","text_ar":"شِعْرٌ شَاعِرٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Excellent poetry:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Sb, T, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"known poetry:"},{"kind":"text","text":"but the former explanation is the more correct. (TA.) One also says, sometimes,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kalimapN $aAEirapN","text_ar":"كَلِمَةٌ شَاعِرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [by"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"klmp","text_ar":"كلمة"},{"kind":"text","text":"] meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaSiydapN","text_ar":"قَصِيدَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": but generally in a phrase of this kind the two words are cognate, as in"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wayolN waAy^ilN","text_ar":"وَيْلٌ وَايِلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"layolN laAy^ilN","text_ar":"لَيْلٌ لَايِلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["T","S","Msb","K","TA","Yoo","Sb"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}